file: crates/ctx-cage/src/error.rs
behavior: Defines the single error type returned by ctx-cage's public API surface, covering I/O failures, JSON (de)serialization failures, and a catch-all protocol/precondition violation.
edit_notes:
  - Protocol variant is a free-form String; new distinct boundary failures should get their own variant only if callers need to match on them, otherwise reuse Protocol with a descriptive message.
  - Richer, module-specific error detail is expected to live on that module's own Result type, not be added here.
functions:
invariants:
  - Io and Json variants are constructed only via #[from] (std::io::Error and serde_json::Error respectively); no manual construction path exists.
external_deps:
  - thiserror: derives Display/Error impls and the #[from] conversions.